			 sys.trusted_assemblies (Transact-SQL) 

					 
								 06/14/2017 
							 2 minutes to read 
							 
								 Contributors 
								 
											 
											 
								 

					 In this article 
						 THIS TOPIC APPLIES TO: SQL Server (starting with 2017) Azure SQL Database Azure SQL Data Warehouse  Parallel Data Warehouse  Contains a row for each trusted assembly for the server. 
   Transact-SQL Syntax Conventions    
 Column name 
 Data type 
 Description 
 hash 
 varbinary(8000) 
 SHA2_512 hash of the assembly content. 
 description 
 nvarchar(4000) 
 Optional user-defined description of the assembly. Microsoft recommends using the canonical name that encodes the simple name, version number, culture, public key, and architecture of the assembly to trust. This value uniquely identifies the assembly on the common language runtime (CLR) side and is the same as the clr_nam